  "original_title": "Sri Lanka guidance peg strengthened despite forex shortages",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka guidance peg strengthened despite forex shortages",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 A guidance peg announced by the central bank for interbank transactions was strengthened 40 cents to 359.30 on June 28, as most economic activities ground to a halt over the inability to import oil due to forex shortages.",
        "forex shortages  Sri Lanka\u2019s bond yields rose over 100 basis points across maturities at this week\u2019s auction, data from the state debt office showed, as the government borrowed 142.3 billion rupees via treasury bonds.",
        "The debt office offered 60 billion rupees of\u00a0bonds\u00a0maturing on 01 June 2025, a 30 billion rupees of bond maturing on 15 January 2028 and a 60 billion rupees of\u00a0bonds\u00a0maturing on 15 May 2031.",
        "Commercial banks were offering dollars for telegraphic transfers at rates between 366.90 and 366.50 for small transactions.",
        "However Sri Lanka cannot import oil and the government asked the public to stay at home until July 10 over the lack of foreign exchange for oil imports through a broken soft-peg.",
        "\u201cThe market has no time to recover with the bond auction today and the bill auction tomorrow,\u201d a dealer said.",
        "At Tuesdays bond auction the 2025 yield moved up from the previous auction while the 2028 was down.",
        "A bond maturing\u00a0on 01.06.2025\u00a0closed at 23.70/80 per cent, up from 21.00/15 at Monday (27) close.",
        "A bond maturing on 15.01.2028 closed at 21.00/60 per cent, up from 20.30/21.00 at Monday (27) close. \u00a0(Colombo/June 28/2022)"
      ],
